author: Karlee Weinmann
title: Option on soccer stadium site expires
text:
Home / News / Economic Development / Option on soccer stadium site expires An option for Minnesota United FC team owners to buy sought-after parcels on Royalston Avenue officially expired Monday. The site is near the Minneapolis Farmers Market and a station on the future Southwest light rail transit line. (File photo: Bill Klotz) Option on soccer stadium site expires By: Karlee Weinmann August 31, 2015 2:54 pm 0 Difficulty swinging Minneapolis Mayor Betsy Hodges in favor of the project and a smoother approval process in St. Paul suggest the stadium could end up elsewhere.
